@node "logs" "LOGS"


                                   LOGS

The log file logs any problems with delivering the mail.  I chose not to log
every transfer as a large list could fill up the logfile quickly. If there is
no bad news, then that is good news.  SUBSCRIBING and UNSUBSCRIBING is also
noted here.

You may do one of three things here.

You can SAVE the log file for later viewing which is a good idea rather than
throwing it away.

You can CLEAR the log, but I suggest that you SAVE it first.  The new log will
be date and time stamped.

You can go back to the MAIN window.


You can even type some text in, although that is not a "feature" per se.
@endnode

