@node "imp" "IMPORTANT"


Some important things to remember when using MM.  First, the program works by
keeping an eye out on UUMAIL: for any alteration.  When something happens to
the drawer then MM scans for the appearence of any file with the same name as
the LIST<#> variable.  When you enter the LOGS mode from the MAIN window, this
feature is still active so of any writing is done to the logs file while you
are in that mode, the window is not updated. Solution? SAVE and CLEAR it
quickly.

When in CNFG mode, the scanning is NOT active.  This is because you might be
changing some of the important settings.  Right now I cannot STOP the mail
process without sending a break process to your SMTPd program. Why not do
this?  Because there is no telling which SMTPd you are using.  Perhaps as I
understand more of the mailing process I will solve this.

Perhaps I will just leave it running next time and no new changes take place
until you return to the main window.

The REPLY-TO headers are set to equal your LIST<#> settings for now so that
receipients need only choose reply from their mail program.  This makes it
easier to reply to the list. It does, however, make it hard to reply to the
PERSON who mailed it.  Anyone with a solution to this problem can mail me,
please.  Is there a header I can set so that they have a choice?

The SENDER header is also set by MM as well.
@endnode

